      <h1>Prevention Tips</h1>
      <p>How to protect yourself from Naegleria fowleri</p>
    </header>

    <main class="content">
      <section class="explanation">
        <h2>How to Prevent Infection</h2>

        <ul class="prevention-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Avoid swimming</strong> in warm, stagnant, or poorly
            maintained freshwater sources like lakes, ponds, and hot springs.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Use nose clips</strong> or hold your nose shut if you must
            swim in freshwater, especially in warm weather.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Never stir up sediment</strong> in shallow, warm freshwater
            — Naegleria fowleri thrives in disturbed sediments.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Keep pool water clean</strong> and well-chlorinated. Regular
            maintenance kills harmful microorganisms.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Do not allow tap water</strong> to go up your nose during
            religious rituals, nasal rinsing (e.g., neti pot), or while bathing.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Boil or filter water</strong> before using it for nasal
            irrigation. Use distilled or sterile water only.
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Educate others</strong> — spreading awareness is a powerful
            form of prevention.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="buttons">
        <a href="nasa.html" class="btn btn-secondary">← Back to Home</a>
      </section>
    </main>

